Falling prices for tickets and hotel 
In the first half of 2008 flights and accommodation in Europe were cheaper than in the previous year. 
Flights in Germany, according to a recent study has even up to 50 per cent cheaper. 
Flights and accommodation at hotels have become cheap again - this is the result of a study by the travel and financial services provider American Express. 
The company has studied his booking data from the first half of 2008, and found after a rise in prices in the first quarter, a sharp drop in the second quarter. 
